The TDD experiment is complete. All 9 tests pass:

1. Empty grid → empty grid
2. Single live cell → empty grid
3. All cells die from underpopulation → empty grid
4. Live cell with 2 neighbors → survives
5. Live cell with 3 neighbors → survives
6. Live cell with more than 3 neighbors → dies
7. Dead cell with exactly 3 neighbors → comes alive
8. Blinker pattern oscillates correctly
9. Block still life remains unchanged

The implementation used a `boolean[][]` sparse representation with bounding box trimming. The refactoring phases extracted two helpers: `findLiveCellBounds` and `willLive`, both improving intent revelation per Simple Design Rules.
